<br>
<br>
i wasnt really too scared. probably because it wasnt something i had learned to have fear of. i'd been out by myself before but not for that long..or not with no food! no peple out that way...and the chances of bear or anything like that werent that great. i was going to go back the second day....but nothing had really happened for me. i was going to make something up..or use some thoughts i had, but i knew someone would know i was lying. <br>
<br>
it all can seem kind of weird to people, but to me it was normal. getting that vision, is a vision for your life. although its not something that is always clear at the time. when its time to have understanding about it...you get it. my grandparents knew what it meant when i told them, but they wouldnt tell me then. <br>
<br>
the vision i had..which is kind of like a dream but you're not asleep...was a hawk or some kind of bird like that, flying from its nest. and it had branches from a thorn bush still stuck in its claws. on the branches were berries and thorns. as the hawk flew up over the mountain there were berries falling from the branches, and the thorns remained. <br>
<br>
it wasnt until just a few years ago it started to make sense. it was when i was thinking of leaving home and i wasnt sure what to do. My grandmother was speaking with me and she asked if i remembered that vision. and i felt it had something to do with me leaving. She said she knew from the time i told her it meant i would leave one day...and that she would live to see it..and it made her sad. but since then she had taught me as one who would be leaving. <br>
<br>
her detailed view of it was this: I was the hawk leaving the nest....that was clear to me. the berries falling had seeds in them and they were planting the bush in areas it never had grown. (this would be the seeds i would plant in other areas about our culture...as a way of sharing it and keeping it alive because if it only grew in that one area eventually it would the bushes would choke themselves out) the thorns remained because they were the pain i would have from leaving home. <br>
<br>
so the vision, when it was made clear in my mind helped me with doing what she had said and what i knew i wanted to do. but was afraid to do.<br>
<br>
my grandparents knew it and from the time i was 16 until a while before i left had been saving money and amking my parents save money..which paid for me to go to classes about computers and communication. the classes were in a city about 80 miles from our home so some of the money was used to buy a jeep so i could drive there and back. <br>
<br>
well that was alot longer of a post then i was thinking of making! but fasting was part of it along with the isolation and having to rely on yourself and what you were taught. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heartjoys>heartjoys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=purple><b>Velvet-Steel Wannabe<br>Shrekjoys</b></font></span><br>  Posts: 2197<br> <font color=#B87333>(1/14/04 9:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fasting</span><hr size=1> I've been reading more on fasting by Bishop Kallistos Ware and thought I'd share some of his quotes:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>On the outward level fasting involves physical abstinence from food and drink, and without such exterior abstinence a full and true fast cannot be kept;  yet the rules about eating and drinking must never be treated as an end in themselves, for ascetic fasting has always an inward and unseen purpose.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The primary aim of fasting is to make us <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>conscious of our dependence upon God.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  If practiced seriously, the Lenten abstinence from food--particularly in the opening days--involves a considerable measure of real hunger, and also a feeling of tiredness and physical exhaustion.  The purpose of this is to lead us in turn to a sense of inward brokeness and contrition;  to bring us, that is, to the point where we appreciate the full force of Christ's statement, &quot;Without Me you can do nothing&quot; (John 15:5 )<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=70.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.threadControl?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=